Choosing the right access tier depends on:

* Frequency of access
* Cost sensitivity
* Data retention requirements
* Performance needs

For example:

* Hot tier for active applications
* Cool tier for backups
* Cold tier for compliance data
* Archive tier for long-term storage

A real-life use case is a company storing recent data in Hot tier and older data in Archive tier.

Another example is log management systems automatically moving data between tiers.

Proper tier selection ensures cost optimization and efficiency.
